    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant equipped with individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing. This example utilizes the desirable ZF 6-speed manual gearbox and a limited-slip M Differential Lock for optimal torque distribution. The chassis has been enhanced with rear subframe reinforcement, addressing the platform's primary structural concern. Mechanically robust, the vehicle maintains excellent throttle response and lateral grip thanks to a refreshed suspension featuring Bilstein dampers and poly-bushes. Though the finish shows minor road-wear consistent with its age, the drivetrain is sorted, with documented rod bearing maintenance and a leak-free cooling system. A true driver\u2019s spec with mechanical longevity at the forefront.",
